He holds the Guinness World Record for the youngest club DJ at just five years and 38 days old. JOHANNESBURG - A South African has become the world's youngest club DJ after performing his first full live set. Oratilwe Hlongwane, who performs under the stage name DJ Arch Jnr, performed a set at a Platinum Lounge Bar in Cosmo City, Johannesburg, He holds the Guinness World Record for the youngest club DJ at just five years and 38 days old. Hlongwane hoped to set the record while on his way to winning South Africa's Got Talent in 2015, but the record requires the attempt take place in a club and last for at least 60 minutes.